ner as his =E2=80=9Celeventh son=E2=80=9D and mentions that the two were at=
 work on some unspecified documentaries. Several sources told me Malnik has=
 very much wanted to help Ratner get back to making movies.

=C2=A0

It
should surprise no one that Malnik happens to be a Mar-a-Lago guy. Last Jun=
e, Modern Luxury Palm Beach ran ( https://mlpalmbeach.com/mar-a-lago-malnik=
-wedding?utm_campaign=3DWhat+I%27m+Hearing+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%282%2F10%2F25%29&=
utm_content=3DWhat+I%27m+Hearing+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%282%2F10%2F25%29&utm_medium=
=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ) a =
photo-heavy piece entitled The Ultimate Palm Beach Wedding at Mar-a-Lago, w=
hich featured the nuptials of Malnik=E2=80=99s son Jarod and his bride, Ale=
xa. Trump put in an appearance beside the happy couple with his familiar th=
umbs-up
pose. It=E2=80=99s not clear whether Malnik had any role in helping Ratner =
get the Melania gig, but perhaps the relationship helped ease the director =
into Trumpworld.

=C2=A0

One source involved with the project wonders whether Beckman, the agent who=
 handled the licensing of the film to Amazon, fully grasped how rancid Ratn=
er=E2=80=99s reputation had become in Hollywood, even apart from the allega=
tions against him. =E2=80=9CI don=E2=80=99t know whether Marc
really knows the breadth of this guy,=E2=80=9D this person said. =E2=80=9CH=
e strikes me as someone who really doesn=E2=80=99t know much about that old=
-school, sordid male world=E2=80=9D that Ratner inhabited.

The Tsujihara
Affair
-------------

Ratner, after all, was closely associated with one of the biggest scandals =
in recent
Hollywood history. Charlotte Kirk, the British aspiring actress who brought=
 down then-Warner Bros. chairman and C.E.O. Kevin Tsujihara and NBCUniversa=
l vice chair Ron Meyer, was able to pursue her Hollywood dreams in the U.S.=
 because, in 2012, Ratner went to bat for her with the Department of Homela=
nd Security. The director wrote that Kirk, then 20, had =E2=80=9Cremarkable=
 talent=E2=80=9D with a =E2=80=9Cunique ability to deliver each of her line=
s seamlessly.=E2=80=9D Kirk got
a special visa, but the problem for both Tsujihara and Meyer was that she w=
as very much not in demand. Despite their powerful jobs, their efforts to h=
elp her land roles failed.

=C2=A0

In 2013, Ratner and Australian billionaire James Packer, then Ratner=E2=80=
=99s partner (the =E2=80=9CPac=E2=80=9D in RatPac Entertainment), introduce=
d Kirk to Tsujihara to celebrate their new $450 million film financing deal
with Warner Bros. Having apparently tired of his own affair with Kirk, acco=
rding to text messages that I previously reported ( https://www.hollywoodre=
porter.com/movies/movie-features/i-need-be-careful-texts-reveal-warner-bros=
-ceo-promoted-actress-apparent-sexual-relationship-1192660/?utm_campaign=3D=
What+I%27m+Hearing+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%282%2F10%2F25%29&utm_content=3DWhat+I%27m=
+Hearing+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%282%2F10%2F25%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_sour=
ce=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ) at The Hollywood Reporter,=
 Packer was ready to pass her along. =E2=80=9CI have the opportunity of a l=
ifetime for u,=E2=80=9D he texted Tsujihara one night in
September 2013. =E2=80=9CCome to [the Hotel] Bel air now. U will never be a=
ble to pay me.=E2=80=9D Meanwhile, he texted Kirk, saying he was going to i=
ntroduce her to =E2=80=9Cthe most important man u can meet.=E2=80=9D

=C2=A0

That led to what Kirk later described as an unpleasant sexual encounter in =
the hotel that night. But she saw the married Tsujihara again, all the whil=
e pressing him to help her find acting jobs. Tsujihara resigned in 2019 aft=
er a former colleague and I reported on his relationship with Kirk. The fol=
lowing year, NBCUniversal fired Meyer because of his own entanglement ( htt=
ps://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movies/movie-news/ron-meyer-nbcuniversal-set=
tlement-charlotte-kirk-1235027252/?utm_campaign=3DWhat+I%27m+Hearing+-+SUBS=
CRIBERS+%282%2F10%2F25%29&utm_content=3DWhat+I%27m+Hearing+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%2=
82%2F10%2F25%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=
=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ) with the actress.

=C2=A0

As she continued to press Tsujihara to help her launch a career, Kirk was r=
epeatedly texting Ratner to demand help finding acting roles. The situation=
 led to a legal confrontation over a confidential settlement Kirk had signe=
d, but an arbitrator took a skeptical view of Kirk=E2=80=99s claim that she=
 was the victim of =E2=80=9Csex trafficking.=E2=80=9D Lawyers for the actre=
ss drafted a complaint alleging that Ratner and associates =E2=80=9Cpassed =
Kirk around like an inanimate sex toy,=E2=80=9D but neither that document n=
or any lawsuit was ever filed. Ratner, via Marty Singer, his lawyer at the =
time, denied everything.

=E2=80=9COut of Whack=E2=80=9D
------------------

The fact that Amazon ended up acquiring Ratner=E2=80=99s film is not withou=
t irony. Roy
Price, the previous head of Amazon Studios, resigned in 2017 due to miscond=
uct allegations that I had started reporting ( https://www.hollywoodreporte=
r.com/news/general-news/amazon-tv-producer-goes-public-harassment-claim-top=
-exec-roy-price-1048060/?utm_campaign=3DWhat+I%27m+Hearing+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%2=
82%2F10%2F25%29&utm_content=3DWhat+I%27m+Hearing+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%282%2F10%2F=
25%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c6061=
7da42abd12a ) even before Weinstein=E2=80=99s downfall. Amazon made a point=
 of replacing Price with a woman, Jen Salke. And when the order came down t=
o license the Melania doc, she was
tasked with the negotiation that would put the studio in business with Ratn=
er.

=C2=A0

Of course, Salke got it done, albeit at a price that was many millions high=
er than what the other two bidders, Disney and Paramount, offered. =E2=80=
=9CI don=E2=80=99t think Jen Salke saw this as a piece of content she had t=
o have,=E2=80=9D said an executive at another studio that made a far more l=
imited offer for the doc. =E2=80=9CAll of it is out of
whack.=E2=80=9D

=C2=A0

Though Prime Video is run by Mike Hopkins, Amazon has several women in top =
jobs in its entertainment operations, in addition to Salke. Marketing chief=
 Sue Kroll will have to sell the doc, and Courtenay Valenti, who oversees t=
heatrical and streaming films, will have to handle its release. Though they=
 would hardly say so publicly, it=E2=80=99s a very safe
bet that none of these women has a scintilla of interest in dealing with th=
is project.

=C2=A0

Yes, everything seems to be out of whack=E2=80=94not just in Hollywood, whi=
ch is still reeling from the streaming revolution, the pandemic, and two st=
rikes=E2=80=94but in Washington and in the world. We have an administration=
 that has barred government employees from forming affinity groups for wome=
n and people of color, a president who blamed a deadly
plane crash on D.E.I. initiatives even before the bodies had been pulled ou=
t of the Potomac, federal agencies that have banned the word =E2=80=9Cfemin=
ism.=E2=80=9D Meanwhile, sexual misconduct allegations don=E2=80=99t even s=
eem to register. So the Ratner movie might also seem to represent a return =
to the bad old days for what used to be called the =E2=80=9Cweaker sex.=E2=
=80=9D He=E2=80=99s pushed for years to make another Rush Hour movie withou=
t success, but we all know how much the studios love their recognizable I.P=
=2E Will
progressive Hollywood allow him back? It=E2=80=99s pretty clear at this poi=
nt that almost anything can happen. It=E2=80=99s enough to make one wonder =
whether Melania still has that jacket=E2=80=94the one reading, =E2=80=9CI r=
eally don=E2=80=99t care. Do u?=E2=80=9D

