Some good notes this week on my Thursday analysis of the Paramount-F.C.C.-T=
rump flap,
and, of course, Baldoni-gate=E2=80=A6

=C2=A0

=E2=80=9CTough to overstate what a shit sandwich Shari [Redstone] will leav=
e the new owners if she settles. That news division will actively try to sa=
botage the new proprietors as it will be seen that their business transacti=
on was =E2=80=98paramount=E2=80=99 to the legacy of CBS News.=E2=80=9D =E2=
=80=94A news executive

=C2=A0

=E2=80=9CYour main points in this piece are absolutely correct. All this is=
 part of the larger=E2=80=94and thus far, remarkably successful=E2=80=94eff=
ort to intimidate and weaken news organizations deemed unsympathetic to the=
 administration. And yes, Brendan Carr can sit on the applications long eno=
ugh to kill the deal. This is antithetical to his past complaints when prio=
r commissioners did not act fast enough to suit him, not to
mention his opposition to content-based regulatory actions. His biggest pol=
itical problem here is setting a precedent that could be used against other=
 broadcasters, such as Fox, Sinclair, and Nexstar. That is why I think he w=
ill let the deal go forward once he and Trump extract what they want from M=
s. Redstone.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94A communications lawyer

=C2=A0

=E2=80=9CWhat=E2=80=99s amazing about the whole [It Ends With Us]
thing is how Baldoni and his producer crew messed up from the get-go. It=E2=
=80=99s Producing 101 to manage creative disagreements. [And] once a film i=
s finished, it is not unusual for a star to recut it. We did a movie with a=
n Oscar-winning director and the star did their own cut, which was better. =
The studio agreed, as did the director and the preview audience. Best cut w=
ins.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94A producer

=C2=A0

=E2=80=9CThe only
explanation that makes any sense is that Justin and Blake are in love with =
