ints when prior commissioners did not act fast enough to suit him, not to
mention his opposition to content-based regulatory actions. His biggest pol=
itical problem here is setting a precedent that could be used against other=
 broadcasters, such as Fox, Sinclair, and Nexstar. That is why I think he w=
